fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.io.writer

Class AbstractWriter<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.inria.atlanmod.neoemf.io.writer.AbstractWriter<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the target
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Handler, Writer
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractStreamWriter, DefaultMapperWriter

    @ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
public abstract class AbstractWriter<T>
extends Object
implements Writer
    An abstract Writer that acts as an accumulator of multi-value features in order to notify them once. This allow to use batch methods in a DataMapper, and ensure the call order when writing in a file.

      • requireEndBeforeFlush

        protected boolean requireEndBeforeFlush()
        Returns true if this writer requires the end of the current element before flushing all features, otherwise, all features will be flushed as soon as another feature is intercepted. This is typically used when writing a structured file with streams.
        Returns:
        true if this writer requires the end of the current element before flushing all features
